description: Global baseline for all generated code
alwaysApply: true
---

# Global Baseline

- Use named exports only in `src`; do not add default exports.
- Prefer `import type` for type-only imports.
- Keep comments sparse and only for non-obvious logic.
- Use early returns and small helpers over deep nesting.
- Keep status/event values centralized in `as const` maps.
- Never let listener callbacks crash runtime loops.
- Run `npm run check` after substantive changes.
- Run `npm run build` when runtime/build-sensitive code changes.
